    "game-obj": "Weapons",
    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "weapon",
        "text": "Another complex gnome invention, the switchscythe is designed for versatility. The curved blade is partly hollow, containing a long rod of wood or metal; the rod can be pulled perpendicular to the blade, turning the switchscythe from a sweeping, axe-like blade into a hooked pick capable of grappling a foe.",
        "level": 1,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Uncommon",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 159,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
                "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "uncommon"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Fatal",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 178,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 282,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "db3dcba30733bab63da3438275614311",
                "text": "The fatal trait includes a die size. On a critical hit, the weapon\u2019s damage die increases to that die size instead of the normal die size, and the weapon adds one additional damage die of the listed size.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ],
                "value": "d10"
            },
            {
                "name": "Gnome",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 80,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 456",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 456",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 456,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "77cc4c8a417cde344d81328245d2cece",
                "text": "A creature with this trait is a member of the gnome ancestry. Gnomes are small people skilled at magic who seek out new experiences and usually have low-light vision. An ability with this trait can be used or selected only by gnomes. A weapon with this trait is created and used by gnomes.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Modular",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 271,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core 2",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
                            "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        },
                        "page": 274,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "1.1",
                            "alt": "1.1",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "34c8c3292092e7f05eaa086e75d06c7c",
                "text": "The weapon has multiple configurations that you can switch between using an Interact action. Typically, switching between configurations of a modular weapon allows it to deal different types of damage (listed in the trait, such as \u201cmodular B, P, or S\u201d), though it's possible for a modular weapon's description to list more complicated configurations.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Interact",
                        "alt": "Interact",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2297
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ],
                "value": "(P and grapple, or S and sweep)"
            }
        ],
